---
import ArrowDown from "./ArrowDown.astro";
---

<section class="bio">
  <h3 class="bio__greeting">Hi there! ðŸ‘‹</h3>

  <p class="bio__text">
    I'm Viktor - a passionate, professional software developer with around 15
    years of experience. I started my career as a QA engineer, confidently move
    to QA Automation and then to Developer role. At the moment I'm a fullstack
    developer but mostly focused on the Frontend, UI and UX. Over the years I
    had a chance to work with a variaty of languages, frameworks, platforms and
    technologies.
  </p>

  <p class="bio__text">
    On my professional journey I've been involved into the success of many
    companies of different sizes and kinds. I've worked for enterprises and
    startups, product companies and outsourcing. As a result I was lucky to gain
    experience in various fields: big media, sports, fin-tech, messengers, and
    even security and a little bit in AI.
  </p>

  <p class="bio__text">
    My goal is to provide a high quality results, solve problems and help
    products to grow.
  </p>

  <p class:list={["bio__text", "last-paragraph"]}>
    Besides my main job, I used to share my expertise and knowledge as a
    Frontend Development Coach at one of the IT Schools helping newcomers to
    start their path in IT.
  </p>

  <ArrowDown id="to-skills-btn" />
</section>

<style>
  .bio {
    min-height: calc(100vh - 60px);
    min-height: calc(100dvh - 60px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .bio__greeting {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    color: var(--clr-text) !important;
  }

  .bio__text {
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .last-paragraph {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.getElementById("to-skills-btn")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    const skillsElem = document.getElementById("skills");
    if (skillsElem) {
      skillsElem.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth" });
    }
  });
</script>
